t;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;font class=&quot;small&quot;&gt;Quote:&lt;/font&gt;&lt;hr /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;i&gt;mavruss said:&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Yes, we are using a SGFC.&amp;nbsp; We closed some of the holes because we couldnt keep the humidity between 95-99% humidity.&amp;nbsp; More like 80-85%&amp;nbsp; We live in dry/cold climate.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;hr /&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;font class=&quot;post&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Never tape the holes.&amp;nbsp; You're restricting free air movement, which lowers humidity as has been proved with dozens of side-by-side tests.&amp;nbsp; Place 1/4&quot; holes 2&quot; apart on all six sides and make sure you have the terrarium elevated off the table it's on so air can enter the bottom.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next></next>\n<prev>17725540</prev>\n<first>17622539</first>\n<last>17725589</last>\n<when>1359736144</when>\n<utime>02/01/13 06:29 PM</utime>\n</post>"}